{"type":"step-attempt","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","sessionId":"480254fe-f57e-4949-ba6a-a64059bce616","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/assurance-profile-spine/cross-boundary-invariants-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/attach/verify-checkpoint.ts","title":"Verification order JSDoc comment does not list the new profile check step","rationale":"The JSDoc comment (lines 52-61) enumerates the verification order but omits the profile self-consistency check inserted at lines 150-169. A future developer reading the comment could miss this step and accidentally reorder it past materialize. The inline comment at line 150 partially compensates, but the function-level JSDoc is the authoritative contract document.","line":52},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/attach/verify-checkpoint.ts","title":"profile-inconsistent fires before profile-uninterpretable for future schema versions","rationale":"The digest check (profile-inconsistent, line 155) runs before the schemaVersion check (profile-uninterpretable, line 163). If a future schemaVersion=2 runtime uses a different digest algorithm, a v1 runtime attaching a v2 checkpoint would emit profile-inconsistent (wrong reason code) instead of profile-uninterpretable. Not reproducible in R1 where schemaVersion=1 is the only value. Latent concern for when schemaVersion=2 is introduced in R2+.","line":155}]},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-16T09:29:35.232Z","endedAt":"2026-07-16T09:38:17.855Z"}
